        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 13 at 1:56PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 156 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms along a line extending from 9 miles southeast of Lamar
to 9 miles northwest of Springfield. Movement was north at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Granada, Bristol, and Two Buttes Reservoir.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
